  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>leek<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> carefully to remove any grit from between the leaves, then top, tail and slice finely</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891381216-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891381216-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891381216-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891381216-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1582891381216-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced leek</strong> and <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891386457-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891386457-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891386457-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891386457-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1582891386457-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve the<strong> vegetable stock mix</strong> in 600ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.2L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once the leek is beginning to soften, add the <strong>arborio rice</strong> and cook for 1 min, stirring to coat the grains in the oil</p><p>Add the <strong>Chinese rice wine</strong>, then slowly add the<strong> vegetable stock</strong> a ladle at a time, stirring continuously for an initial 15 min</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891390008-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891390008-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891390008-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891390008-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1582891390008-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, reboil half a kettle</p><p>Tear the <strong>dill </strong>roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>blanched</strong> <strong>peas</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over them</p><p>Add <strong>most </strong>of the <strong>peas</strong> (save some for garnish!) to a <strong>food processor</strong> with the <strong>torn</strong> <strong>dill</strong>, <strong>soft cheese</strong> and<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and blitz into a purée – this is your <strong>pea purée</strong></p>",
